"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xnr1665702825556.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xnr1665702825556.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xnr1665702825556.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xnr1665702825556\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Import Repository Objects\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copy development object definitions from an export file into your Repository.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xnr1665702825556__section_w25ab1b7b1_w26ab1b7_w27ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xnr1665702825556__section_w28ab1b7b3_w29ab1b7_w30ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d277042e60\">\n                  \n Fields\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnr1665702825556__p_d8567e1_d8568e1_d8569e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File Name</span>—enter or select the name of file of the XML file to import.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnr1665702825556__p_d8570e1_d8571e1_d8572e1\">You must have read permission for the files you import. You also need to have read and write permission for all the Repository entities to which Uniface writes during the import process.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xnr1665702825556__section_w31ab1b7b5_w32ab1b7_w33ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d277042e75\">\n                  \n How to\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnr1665702825556__p_d8576e1_d8577e1_d8578e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"adn1665702696511.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/adn1665702696511.html\" title=\"It is only possible to import development objects that have been exported from a compatible Uniface Repository. Data is considered compatible if it comes from the same Repository version, or if it can be migrated to the current Repository.\">Import Development Objects</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533814\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533814\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Import Repository Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Import Repository Objects Copy development object definitions from an export file into your Repository. Fields File Name —enter or select the name of file of the XML file to import. You must have read permission for the files you import. You also need to have read and write permission for all the Repository entities to which Uniface writes during the import process. How to Import Development Objects Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}